Describe a place in the countryside that you visited
- where it is
- when you visited this place
- what you did there
- and explain how you feel about this place

I'm going to talk about a beautiful river that I visited when I went to my best friend's hometown about three years ago.
At that time, I had just finished my final exams in my fourth year at university, so I had a few weeks off. To help me relax after a stressful semester, my friend invited me to visit her hometown, which is a rural district in the western part of Vietnam. I gladly accepted, as I really wanted a break from city life.
Her hometown was absolutely picturesque, with vast stretches of rice fields and rolling hills in the distance. During my three-day stay, she showed me around several local attractions, but the place that left the strongest impression on me was a river we visited every afternoon.
Althoulgh I can no longer remember its name, I still vividly recall its beauty. The river was quite wide and deep, and even though the water wasn't perfectly clear, it had a soft blue hue that made it especially appealing. What I loved most was its calmness. The surface of the water was usually still creating a peaceful and relaxing atmosphere.
I particularly enjoyed walking along the riverbank. With the cool breeze on my face and the soothing sound of water flowing beside me, I felt completely at ease. It was the perfect escape from the hustle and bustle of city life.
Overall, it was one of the most memorable experiences I've ever had, and I'm actually planning to revisit this place sometime this year to relive those wonderful moments.
